AGI - Hundreds of people went on the road in the evening in the Jabalia refugee camp, > in the west of the City of Gaza >, to protest against Hamas> and ask for the end of the war. As reported by the Times of Israel, the crowd raised shouts: "We want to eat."
In the afternoon a hundred people protested at Beit Lahia, in the north of the Gaza Strip, always against Hamas.&nbsp; "Hamas outside" or "Hamas terrorist" shouted the protesters at Beit Lahia. >
Israel resumed military operations in Gaza on 18 March, after breaking the truce signed in mid-January. According to health sources in Al Jazeera. 37 Palestinians were killed today in Idf attacks in the Strip.&nbsp;

